			<div class="comment-content"><p>Prof. Perry,</p>
<p>Index the revenue to Nominal GDP (rather than merely inflation), for an even starker chart&#8230;</p>
<p>Revenue being the same as 1950 is much worse than it sounds, given that Real GDP grew 3.2%/year over that time (and thus Real GDP is 8x higher).  The 2013 number, as a share of Nominal GDP (Real GDP + the already-included inflation), would be very, very much lower than the 1950 number&#8230;</p>
</div>

